Ad Text:
We are oOh!media (pronounced “oh!” media). 

oOh!media is the #1 Out of Home company in Australia and New Zealand.  

We exist to make public spaces better and brands unmissable, proudly leading the market with innovation, creativity, data and results. Our network plays an important role in the communities they are located, creating engaging environments that inform, entertain and inspire, while connecting brands with audiences at scale.  

We are oOh!media, and we are unmissable.

Join us:  

We’re a team driven by creativity, innovation, and a sense of community. We show up every day ready to be bold, brave, and push the boundaries of Out of Home advertising. You’ll work alongside a group of talented individuals across Australia and New Zealand, all of whom are dedicated to raising the bar. If you’re ready to realize your potential and make an impact, join us. 

About the opportunity:

 Permanent role
Based in North Sydney

We are seeking a hands-on AI Solutions Engineer to join our Engineering team and act as the technical builder responsible for turning AI hypotheses into secure, scalable prototypes and automations.

This role is the bridge across data, platform, and product domains, connecting systems, data, and intelligence. You will blend rapid experimentation with disciplined engineering, ensuring AI prototypes are built safely, run reliably, and can evolve into long-term industrial capabilities.

If you are a problem-solver and tinkerer who thrives on figuring out how to connect systems and automate workflows, this is your chance to make a massive impact.

Key responsibilities and experience:

Building Tactical AI Solutions: Translate user stories into working AI workflows, automations, and copilots. You will build and connect data pipelines, APIs, and low-code components across systems.
Prototyping & Experimentation: Safely experiment with emerging frameworks, including LLMs, Agentic systems, and RAG architectures.
Security & Governance: Apply responsible AI principles and ensure solutions comply with InfoSec and privacy standards.
Data Connectivity: Ensure secure and efficient data access (read, transform, integrate) across all solutions.

You will also have:

3–6 years in Data, Platform, or Automation Engineering.
Skilled in SQL, APIs, and low-code/no-code platforms (e.g., Power Automate, Logic Apps, Zapier).
Familiarity with Python/JavaScript for glue code and LLM integration.
Experience integrating SaaS tools (e.g., CRM, CMS, BI, Data Warehousing).
Experience with AWS, Azure, M365, and data governance standards.
Familiarity with RAG, Agentic systems, and MCP frameworks.
Detail-oriented, secure by design, and disciplined with data.
A fast learner who stays current with emerging AI tools and frameworks.
A natural collaborator comfortable partnering with non-technical peers.

Bonus: Experience with DataBricks is an advantage.




Our benefits and perks:

Competitive salary package 
A positive, supportive workplace culture 
Professional growth and development opportunities 
Comprehensive, paid training and ongoing support 

If you’re curious, ready for a unique challenge, and want to make a real impact, we want to hear from you! 

At oOh!, we celebrate diversity and strive for an inclusive environment. We welcome applications from all backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with disabilities, LGBTQIA+ individuals, and refugees. 

To be considered, applicants must be Australian citizens or permanent residents with full working rights in Australia, and all offers of employment are subject to employer-funded pre-employment checks including police, reference, and work rights verification, with additional checks such as credit, bankruptcy, drug and alcohol screening, or driver’s licence verification required for some roles.

Ad Text:

The data analytics engineer position focuses on improving the efficiency, reliability, and scalability of data collation processes by developing and maintaining tools and systems that streamline data ingestion, validation, transformation, and integration of data from eight jurisdictions to compile a national data set. 

Operating under limited supervision, you will lead technical workstreams, apply your engineering and analytical skills to solve complex data problems, and collaborate with internal stakeholders and jurisdictional data providers to ensure solutions are fit-for-purpose, secure, and aligned with national data standards. 

This role requires a balance of strong technical capabilities, project coordination skills, and the ability to work effectively with diverse stakeholders in a complex intergovernmental environment.

Under general direction you will:

Analyse existing data collation processes and identify opportunities for automation and improvement, for compiling a national data set from eight jurisdictional supplies (improve data flows, reduce manual effort, and automate key processes).
Design, develop, and maintain automated data pipelines and workflows to collect, validate, and integrate data from eight jurisdictional sources into a national system. The pipelines should be scalable, reliable, efficient, and aligned with relevant Institute wide initiatives (see last point).
Implement robust data validation, transformation, and quality assurance procedures using engineering and programming best practices.
Collaborate with data providers and internal stakeholders (including analysts and ICT) to define and document technical requirements, data standards, and business rules.
Provide advice, technical support (including user guides), and training to uplift staff capability in modern data workflows.
Document processes and promote reusable solutions to ensure sustainability and efficiency across the Institute.
Provide expert advice and support Institute wide process optimisation, automation and analytics environment modernisation initiatives.

How to apply

Please submit your application online via the AIHW e-Recruit system using this link. When applying online for the first time, you will need to register and provide a valid email address.

Your application must include:

A summary of your relevant skills and experience and explain why you would be the best person for
the role. Your response should align with the position summary and selection criteria information above, and must be no more than 750 words.
Your current CV and the names of two referees

As LMA continues to expand its Australian portfolio, we’re growing our team of talented Integration Engineers.
In this role, you’ll take software builds from the development team and deploy them into integration environments and mission systems, supporting the development and uplift of the Software Integration Lab. You’ll work across software, hardware and infrastructure to ensure seamless performance in complex operational environments.

Key responsibilities include:

Integrate, deploy and maintain complex Defence systems across multi-domain environments.

Set up, maintain and monitor integration environments and mission systems.
Implement and manage CI/CD pipelines, automation and Infrastructure as Code (IaC).

Support configuration, audit activities and continuous improvement.

Work within an agile team to plan, test and demonstrate system functionality and readiness.

 

About you:

​​​​​​​You’re an experienced integration engineer who thrives in mission-critical, multi-domain environments. You’re confident working across software, hardware, ICT networks, Linux systems and modern DevSecOps pipelines. You bring:

Strong experience in Systems Integration and Test & Evaluation.

Expertise in Linux administration, networking, scripting and automation.

Hands-on experience with CI/CD, IaC (Ansible, Terraform) and containerisation (Kubernetes, Docker).

Experience in Defence or similarly complex engineering programs.

Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with a collaborative mindset.

A degree in Engineering or equivalent relevant experience

At Intelligen, we’re building something different. Over the past three years, we’ve evolved from a bold startup to a trusted partner for some of Australia’s most complex data transformations. We’ve helped organisations move from legacy to modern platforms, embedded governance into decision-making, and brought AI into the hands of the business - responsibly and at speed.

But we’re just getting started. As we move into our next phase of growth, we’re looking for consultants who don’t just want to deliver great solutions - but help shape the future of data and AI capability across Australia.

About the Opportunity...

We’re looking for a Data Engineer, based in Melbourne, who can design and deliver modern, scalable data solutions across multi-cloud environments (AWS, GCP, Azure) and modern data stacks such as Databricks, Snowflake, dbt, and cloud-native services.

You’ll work directly with clients to understand their data challenges, architect and build high-quality pipelines, and support analytics, governance, and AI enablement initiatives. This role blends hands-on engineering with consulting - helping clients realise value at pace while contributing to Intelligen’s growing engineering capability.

This role is ideal for someone who loves solving complex engineering problems, thrives in modern data ecosystems, and wants to work in a high-performing team doing meaningful, future-shaping work.

What You’ll Do

Design, build, and optimise scalable, reliable data pipelines across cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure)
Work with modern data technologies such as Databricks, Snowflake, cloud data lakes, and orchestration tools
Develop high-quality data models to support analytics, reporting, and AI use cases
Collaborate with clients to translate business requirements into well-structured, actionable data solutions
Implement data ingestion, transformation, storage, and access layers across multi-cloud environments
Support or implement dbt, CI/CD, and engineering best practices across projects
Ensure strong data quality, governance, lineage, and performance practices
Contribute to reusable components, accelerators, and internal engineering frameworks
Work closely with cross-functional consultants, analysts, and architects to deliver cohesive solutions
Mentor junior engineers and positively influence client delivery

What You’ll Bring

Curiosity and a problem-solving mindset. You enjoy understanding how things work and making them better.
A commitment to clean, scalable engineering practices and continuous learning
A collaborative spirit. You enjoy working across teams to deliver real outcomes.The confidence to share ideas, challenge the norm, and help build something better.


Requirements


4–6+ years’ experience in data engineering or analytics engineering
Strong hands-on experience with Databricks, and at least one major cloud platform (AWS, GCP, or Azure)
Solid SQL capability and experience building complex data transformations
Familiarity with modern data stacks - e.g., Snowflake, dbt, Delta Lake, cloud ETL/orchestration tools
Experience working across the full data lifecycle: ingestion → transformation → modelling → consumption
Consulting, stakeholder-facing experience, or cross-functional delivery exposure
Knowledge of DevOps concepts, version control, and/or CI/CD in data environments
Excellent communication, problem-solving, and collaboration skills
Melbourne-based, with ability to work on-site with clients as required
A mindset of curiosity, delivery excellence, and continuous learning


Benefits



We’re not just delivering AI and data projects, we’re humanising them. That means we care deeply about the how, not just the what. We value curiosity, creativity, and a willingness to challenge the status quo. We look for people who are driven to build a business, get curious, and offer up their opinions and ideas.

As well as:

Work From Home - Flexible hours
Training & Development
Free Food & Snacks
Many socials and community groups
Opportunity to drive projects that are of interest to you!

You’ll work with a team that’s smart, kind, and ambitious. You’ll have real influence in your projects, your practice, and our business. And as we grow, so will you.

Lead the build of enterprise-scale Generative AI solutions

We’re looking for a standout AI + Cloud Engineer to join us on a 12-month contract and help deliver cutting-edge Generative AI capabilities across the business. If you love solving complex problems with cloud-native tech and modern AI frameworks, this role is for you.

What You’ll Do
Design and deliver enterprise-ready GenAI solutions.
Build and orchestrate multi-agent AI systems.
Ensure security, reliability, and observability across deployments.
Develop full-stack applications with solid automated testing.
Use AWS, DevOps, CI/CD and modern AI tooling to ship at scale.

Competitive rates + cutting-edge tech + real enterprise scale.

About the job
Google's software engineers develop the next-generation technologies that change how billions of users connect, explore, and interact with information and one another. Our products need to handle information at massive scale, and extend well beyond web search. We're looking for engineers who bring fresh ideas from all areas, including information retrieval, distributed computing, large-scale system design, networking and data storage, security, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, UI design and mobile; the list goes on and is growing every day. As a software engineer, you will work on a specific project critical to Google’s needs with opportunities to switch teams and projects as you and our fast-paced business grow and evolve. We need our engineers to be versatile, display leadership qualities and be enthusiastic to take on new problems across the full-stack as we continue to push technology forward.Google Photos is a photo sharing and storage service developed by Google. Photos is one of the most sought after products at Google and is looking for both client-side (web and mobile), with server-side (search, storage, serving) and machine intelligence (learning, computer vision) Software Engineers. We are dedicated to making Google experiences centered around the user.
